The piezoelectric coefficients in reduced form in equation (35) are not equal to those in standard 3-D form in equation (34). These reduced coefficients can be derived from the elastic modulus and the dielectric permittivity of the piezoelectric material. The following constitute relations for {3-1} operating mode,47 are given by
(36)big{c11E=S11E(S11E)2-(S12E)2e31=S11Ed31-S12Ed31(S11E)2-(S12E)2ɛ33S=ɛ33T-2d312(S11E-S12E)(S11E)2-(S12E)2}
where s is the elastic compliance constant, which is the reciprocal of elastic/Young’s modulus and d the piezoelectric constant. The superscript T denotes the corresponding parameters at a constant mechanical stress.
